    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="700"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/9–1444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 3, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2656. The cable below is WRB 101. Please refer to your No. 2875 of September 14
                    (WRB 189).<note n="17" xml:id="d700fn17">Not printed; it concerned question of
                        destination of refugees admitted to Portugal (840.48
                        Refugees/9–1444).</note>
                </p>
                <p>As you were advised in Department’s No. 2118 of July 28<note n="18"
                        xml:id="d700fn18">Not printed, but see telegram 5948, July 28, midnight, to
                        London, <ref target="#pg_1106">p. 1106</ref>.</note> and 2332 of August
                        24,<note n="19" xml:id="d700fn19">Not printed, but see telegram 2918, August
                        24, 7 p.m., to Bern, <ref target="#pg_1135">p. 1135</ref>.</note> this
                    Government has guaranteed that it will arrange for the maintenance in Portugal
                    and the removal to the United States or to other areas outside Portugal of all
                    refugees who are admitted to Portugal in accordance with the terms of those
                    cables. It is the firm intention of this Government to comply fully with the
                    terms of this guarantee, should the necessity arise. Until the number of such
                    refugees and other similar facts are known, it is neither possible nor desirable
                    to determine exactly where they will be taken. You may assume that all available
                    havens, including Fedhala, will be used to fulfill this Government’s
                    guarantee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
